explanation: The algorithm iteratively compares the first character of s and the last character of t. It appends the smaller character to t and removes the corresponding character from s or t. This process continues until both strings are empty, building the lexicographically smallest string p.  The time complexity is linear as each character is processed at most once. The space complexity is also linear due to the potential size of the resulting string p. Energy implications are low as the algorithm performs constant-time operations.

